#!/usr/bin/env bash
# Configures Nginx with a 301 redirect on /redirect_me to a YouTube page
export DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive
apt-get update -y
apt-get install -y nginx

echo 'Holberton School for the win!' > /var/www/html/index.html
echo 'Holberton School for the win!' > /var/www/html/index.nginx-debian.html

sed -i '/server_name _;/a \\n\tlocation \/redirect_me {\n\t\treturn 301 https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=QH2-TGUlwu4;\n\t}' /etc/nginx/sites-available/default

service nginx start
service nginx reload
```

The key here is using `sed` to insert **multiple lines** after `server_name _;` in the default config — which is exactly what the readme hint is pointing at. It adds:
```
location /redirect_me {
    return 301 https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=QH2-TGUlwu4;
}
